<html t:type="layout" title="Try twitt2opo"
	xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd"
	xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">

	<h1 style="text-align: center">Try twitt2opo</h1>
	<br />
	
	<p id="text">
		Bellow you have a field where you can type in a Twitter profile name for which you want the 
		OPO representation to be made. In case that user's twitts are protected, you'll need to 
		explicitly grant this application permissions to access your twitts. But don't worry, that 
		access is completely safe and secure for you because it is made via 
		<a href="http://oauth.net/" target="_blank">oAuth protocol</a>.
	</p>
	<br/><br/>
	
	<div style="text-align: center">
			<form t:type="Form" t:id="convertForm"><t:errors />
				<t:label t:for="userName"></t:label>: <input t:id="userName" t:type="TextField" 
								t:value="username" t:validate="required"/>
					
				<br/><br/>		
				<input id="convert_submit_button" type="submit" value=""/>
			</form>
	</div>
	
	<br/><br/>
	
	<p id="text">
		After clicking <b>"Allow me access!"</b> button, if the account has protected twitts, 
		another window will pop up and by clicking <b>"Allow"</b> you will allow twitt2opo to 
		read your Twitter profile data, needed for this conversion.
	</p>
</html>
